and its empire by dying emperor Marcus Aurelius, so that rule might pass from the Caesars back to the people and Senate. Marcus' 
neglected and power-hungry son, Commodus, has other ideas, however. Escaping an ordered execution, Maximus hurries back to his home 
in Spain, too late to save his wife and son from the same order. Taken into slavery and trained as a gladiator by Proximo, Maximus 
lives only that he might someday take his revenge and fulfill the dying wish of his emperor. The time soon comes when Proximo's 
troupe is called to Rome to participate in a marathon of gladiator games held at the behest of the new emperor, Commodus. Once in 
